HEADWORD: Filar
<hw>Fi"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>filum</ets> a
thread.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a thread or line; characterized
by threads stretched across the field of view; <as>as, a <ex>filar</ex>
microscope; a <ex>filar</ex> micrometer.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filaria</ent>⟦br⟧
